data.title: The Swedes kicked Ostersunds into the Third League
data.meta_description: The club has announced that it will appeal this decision, but first it has to raise $XNUMX million to pay off loans and taxes
data.text:
The Swedish Football Association refused to grant Ostersunds a license to compete in the First League next season.

So, due to financial problems, instead of in the elite, they will play in the third tier - Division 1.

"Ostersunds does not meet the criteria", is the message from FS Sweden.

The club has announced that it will appeal this decision, but first it has to raise $XNUMX million to pay off loans and taxes.

The former president of Ostersunds, Danijel Kindberg, was recently sentenced to three years in prison for money laundering, and it was stated in the verdict that with the help of two other people and three companies, he illegally brought about 1,3 million dollars into the club.

Ostersunds became a sensation under Kindberg's command, because in a short time they went from the amateur level to the 1/16 finals of the Europa League, where they were eliminated by Arsenal.

Kindberg took over the club in 2011 while it was in the Fourth League, five years later it entered the Alsvenskan (First League), and in 2017 it won the Cup...
